description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Administrative Assistant - Professional Development Nursing Team &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and dynamic individual to work as part of the Corporate Nursing team. You will provide a wide range of administration and clerical support to the Lead Nurses for Education and Quality and the Professional Development Nursing teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post requires a confident and autonomous person who can ensure robust processes are followed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have resilience and take pride in personal responsibility for your work as well as being a team player. You will need to be able to work in a busy environment where you can balance competing demands and where priorities frequently change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are required to have current or very recent experience of working in an administrative /Secretarial role. Experience of working in the NHS is an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have excellent written and communication skills, be organised, and self-motivated, with the ability to work to tight deadlines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers an excellent opportunity for an individual wants to take the next steps to progress and or develop their career. The role will provide the post holder with exposure and experience in gaining a wide range of skills and knowledge. You will work with a supportive team in a positive environment for learning and development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work their hours flexibly over a 3- 4 day working week (between 22.5 and 27.5 hours), Monday to Friday, being required to travel and work at both the Royal Shrewsbury and the Princess Royal Hospital when required .&lt;/p&gt;
